name: ImportOrganizationUnits
description:
Creates or updates specified `OrganizationUnits`, identified by your `ID` (that we map to our `BackendID`).

Omit any field you don't want altered, or send in null values of nullable fields to unset their current value.

- Does not apply to `Address` - if you specify a new or different one from the current, a new Address will be created with only the data specify!
- Does not apply to `OpeningHours` - every value you specify will either update or create a record for that day
auth_description: Requires a user of type `Employee` or `Api` with functionality `ImportOrganizationUnits:None`

headers.name: EVA-User-Agent
headers.description: The user agent that is making these calls. Don't make this specific per device/browser but per application. This should be of the form: `MyFirstUserAgent/1.0.0`

headers.name: EVA-Requested-OrganizationUnitID
headers.description: The ID of the organization unit to run this request in.

headers.name: EVA-Requested-OrganizationUnit-Query
headers.description: The query that selects the organization unit to run this request in.

headers.name: EVA-IDs-Mode
headers.description: The IDs mode to run this request in. Currently only `ExternalIDs` is supported.
